OL,4,Cprocedure by hospital trainee, inquest
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FThey continued: "Aarav's death is a
OL,8,Floss that will stay with us forever.
OL,10,F"There is a void and emptiness in our
OL,11,Flives that will never be filled.
OL,13,F"Knowing that Aarav's death was
OL,14,Fpreventable had appropriate action
OL,15,Fbeen taken makes the situation even
OL,16,Fharder to accept."
OL,18,F"No joined-up discussion"
